					Title: <b>Disc usage</b><br />
					Post by: <b>MORA</b> on <b>February 18, 2013, 10:22:51 AM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">Over the last 2 years, I have been running a bitcoin service.<br />Now the disc usage is getting out of hand, and I am wondering if there is any improvements in that in newer versions?<br /><br />The one I am running is quite old (it does not have access to any bitcoins), and since I am using a custom patch, it may not be so simple to upgrade.<br /><br />Also what amount of disc usage is acceptable atm ?<br /><br />Currently I have 20GB used just by .bitcoin :(</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Disc usage</b><br />
					Post by: <b>grue</b> on <b>February 20, 2013, 03:00:22 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">20 gb?? my %appdata%\bitcoin is only 6 GB, plus a few megabytes for the binaries.</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Disc usage</b><br />
					Post by: <b>DannyHamilton</b> on <b>February 21, 2013, 02:49:34 PM</b>
